  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to determine whether hemodynamic optimization with
      photoplethysmography (ClearSight, Edwards Lifesciences, Irvine, CA) during colorectal surgery
      could decrease the incidence of perioperative complications.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      All patients received the photoplethysmography monitoring, but the monitor was blinded in the
      control group.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
